restaurantList.name: Restaurant Bougainville
restaurantList.address: Dam 27 In Hotel TwentySeven, 1012 JS Amsterdam The Netherlands

restaurantList.name: Midtown Grill
restaurantList.description: Expect a fine dining experience at Midtown Grill. Our steakhouse restaurant in Amsterdam features high-quality cuts of meat from around the world. Don't miss our weekend brunch, every Saturday and Sunday from 12:30pm to 5:00pm.

photo.caption: Sit in the open kitchen and enjoy a talk with our chefs while they are cooking your steak to perfection.

restaurantList.address: Stadhouderskade 12, 1054 ES Amsterdam The Netherlands

restaurantList.name: Ku Kitchen & Bar
restaurantList.description: Ku Kitchen & Bar opened in 2014 and has been a buzzing bar and restaurant ever since. Located on one of the prettiest streets in Amsterdam, the Utrechtsestraat. We have weekly changing specials and classics. Sushi, wagyu burgers and lots of vegetarian options.
restaurantList.address: Utrechtsestraat 114, 1017 VT Amsterdam The Netherlands

restaurantList.name: de Silveren Spiegel
restaurantList.description: Elegance, tradition and hospitality are the core traits of one of Amsterdam’s finest restaurants, de Silveren Spiegel (the Silver Mirror). The restaurant dates from the Dutch Golden Age, the 17th century, so you can experience the ambiance of this time period. Breathtaking surroundings and a lovely diner. Private rooms for special occasions, parties or business meetings available.
restaurantList.address: Kattengat 4-6, 1012 SZ Amsterdam The Netherlands

restaurantList.name: Kroegtijger
restaurantList.description: De Kroegtijger (roughly translated: café tiger/ frequenter of a café) is a traditional Dutch brown café turned modish hangout. Tucked away in the historic heart of Amsterdam, among the city's infamous red-lit windows and Chinese food joints, De Kroegtijger is a warm and welcoming bar with a small-town, unpretentious feel. It's the ideal destination for anyone out on their own, for sharing a drink with close friends, or for celebrating a special occasion. Showcasing unique aspects of local culture, De Kroegtijger serves all your usual favorites, as well as a superb selection of micro brews and indie offerings. Want a next level cocktail? Or an authentic Dutch 'kopstootje'? The owners'll get your drinks flowing, dim the lights and turn up the music!
restaurantList.address: Zeedijk 134, 1012 BC Amsterdam The Netherlands

restaurantList.name: Senses Restaurant
restaurantList.description: Senses is a warm and intimate restaurant with an open kitchen where 'food art' that ignites the senses is created. Chef Lars Bertelsen specialises in creating unconventional menus, which highlight the culinary artistry of the chef and his team. His menus all tell a story and contain unexpected combinations. The dishes are made using the freshest seasonal and where possible, sustainable ingredients. Let your senses be stimulated and opt for the unexpected. Choose from the weekly alternating 3 to 7-course surprise menu and embark on your own voyage of discovery. Chef Lars Bertelsen and his team look forward to giving you a tantalizing and delightful culinary experience!
restaurantList.address: Vijzelstraat 45, 1017 HE Amsterdam The Netherlands

restaurantList.name: Boaz Amsterdam
restaurantList.description: Boaz Amsterdam, a small day restaurant in the Jordaan (former Visser Amsterdam). We are open for breakfast, coffee, lunch & drinks. Boaz is also available for private dining (dinner, parties etc.) and check our calendar for special evening programme with "chef in residence", an evening with nice dinner menu with pairing wines.
restaurantList.address: Lindengracht 95 H, 1015 KD Amsterdam The Netherlands

restaurantList.name: Ta Toru
restaurantList.description: We are a Moluccan inspired saté/snackbar with a twist. We get our inspiration from all over the world. Our mission is to bring you our authentic flavors from the Moluccan in a modern dish. We hope to see you soon!
restaurantList.address: Nieuwezijds Voorburgwal 182I The Food Department, 1012 SJ Amsterdam The Netherlands

restaurantList.name: Utrechtsedwarstafel
restaurantList.description: AN EXPERIENCE. Within strolling distance from Theatre Carré there is the stage of Hans Verbeek and Esther van Meerten, the two culinary artists from restaurant Utrechtsedwarstafel. Their performance is a ballet of wine and food. Indulge yourself with the culinary compositions by Esther the Chef and the wines of Sommelier Winemaster Hans. This is the best restaurant dining experience in Amsterdam. An adventurous evening
restaurantList.address: Utrechtsedwarsstraat 107-109, 1017 WD Amsterdam The Netherlands

restaurantList.name: Graham's Kitchen
restaurantList.description: Fine dining tasting menu with choice of 3-6 dishes with a very personal touch in a relaxing atmosphere.
restaurantList.address: Hemonystraat 38, 1074 BS Amsterdam The Netherlands

restaurantList.name: Day's StoneGrill 1870
restaurantList.description: DAY'S StoneGrill 1870 is a steakhouse where you can go for lunch and dinner. The pieces of meat come from all over the world, such as Argentina, New Zealand and Canada. The menu specializes in grill dishes as in steaks, burgers and seafood. We also have a lot of vegan options. You can choose a side dish with every entree from DAY'S StoneGrill 1870, such as French fries, rice or vegetables. At DAY'S StoneGrill 1870's bar, all kinds of beer, wines and spirits such as vodka, rum and whiskeys are served. Here you have the option to grill as in 1870. We prepare all meat dishes perfectly from the kitchen and you can grill it at the table. If it's a nice, sunny day, you can enjoy your meal outside on the covered patio.
restaurantList.address: Spuistraat 4, 1012 TS Amsterdam The Netherlands

restaurantList.name: Sherpa Restaurant
restaurantList.description: Sherpa Restaurant, founded in 1989 in Amsterdam, is the first Nepalese and Tibetan restaurant in the Netherlands. We also serve several signature Indian cuisines. Traditional cooking in Nepal, Tibet, and India is an art and requires years of experience. Nepalese cuisine consists of mainly curries and rice and prepared with mild spices and herbs. Similarly, Tibetan dishes consist of various Momos (dumplings) and noodles and prepared mainly with Himalayan herbs. Furthermore, Indian dishes consist of various Curries, Tandoori, Biryani, Naan, and Roti. All our dishes are freshly prepared in order to offer you an authentic taste and freshness. Please don't hesitate to ask us about your special choices.

photo.caption: Perfect choice of Veg and Non veg. Chicken Karahi and Paneer Butter Masala.

restaurantList.address: Korte Leidsedwarsstraat 58, 1017 RD Amsterdam The Netherlands

restaurantList.name: Hearth
restaurantList.description: Plant-based Restaurant- Audio Bar In the old houses HEARTH was a fireplace made of stone used for heating and cooking. It was the vital center of the house and its most important feature. Our purpose is to create a warm and creative space where people can hangout and connect. We serve fusion plant-based dishes uniquely created in house by our chef. We host live jazz event and listening session with local and international talents.

photo.caption: Handmade Vegan Parsnip Gnocchi with Yellow Courgette Pesto and Cashews Tarragon Cheese

restaurantList.address: Camperstraat 26H, 1091 AG Amsterdam The Netherlands

restaurantList.name: Teppanyaki Restaurant Sazanka
restaurantList.description: Welcome to Teppanyaki Restaurant Sazanka, sizzling with life. Amidst a vibrant and sociable atmosphere, guests gather around expert Japanese teppanyaki chefs as they prepare sumptuous dishes with flair and precision on hot iron griddles, right before diners’ eyes. Ancient traditions and contemporary Japanese cuisine are exacted to the highest level at Sazanka. Top quality ingredients are complemented by an extensive choice of sakes and wines, while staff provide world-class Japanese service. Tucked away from the main restaurant, Sazanka’s private dining room offers a more intimate experience, heightening the skill and excitement of superb teppanyaki.
restaurantList.address: Ferdinand Bolstraat 333 Hotel Okura, 1072 LH Amsterdam The Netherlands

restaurantList.name: Restaurant Zaza's
restaurantList.description: Restaurant Zaza’s, owned by Susie Roche from Ireland, opened its doors in May 2003 in the heart of “De Pijp”, Amsterdam’s Latin Quarter and hot spot for socialising. Susie and her team – Chef Cook Dave, Jasper, Noury, Ijsbrand, Rachael and Marina have a passion for their work and share a love of good food and great service. Zaza’s is a small, intimate restaurant with just 12 tables, serving an International menu of fresh, homemade culinary delights with influences from France, The Mediterranean and Asia which changes with the seasons. The theme “Absolutely Fabulous” (taken from the well-known English comedy series) is about enjoying life to the full and above all having fun. So whether it’s a business dinner, an “Ab Fab” evening to remember, starting with a glass of Champagne (‘Darling!’) or simply relaxing and making yourself at home with a glass of wine…… Zaza’s welcomes you! fabulous darlings!
restaurantList.address: Daniel Stalpertstraat 103, 1072 XD Amsterdam The Netherlands

restaurantList.name: Ava Cyril
restaurantList.description: A cosy restaurant with an open kitchen in the center of Amsterdam (minutes away from Central Station). Our concept: the customer is part of our family and we make our food with love. We hope to see you at our restaurant!
restaurantList.address: Nieuwendijk 46 hs, 1012 MN Amsterdam The Netherlands

restaurantList.name: Pesca
restaurantList.description: Making fish accessible again! That’s what we do. Over the last few years the popularity of fish has skyrocketed as more and more people have become aware of the importance of diverse and healthy eating. However, there is still a feeling of frustration. Where can you find good quality fish for a good price in a cozy environment nowadays? It was time for change! We make fish accessible for everyone in a different way. Don’t expect a traditional restaurant when you open the doors to Pesca. We have thrown out all the old rules: no more menus, white linen or table service. It is all about the experience in the fish market where you get to choose your fish and side dishes! We have a dynamic pricing policy on the fish market. During the day, the fishmongers continuously decrease the price of the fish to sell out all the fish we have available. In this way we avoid unnecessary food waste. Are you ready for the show? Welcome to our theatre of fish: Pesca!
restaurantList.address: Rozengracht 133, 1016 LV Amsterdam The Netherlands

restaurantList.name: Restaurant Adam
restaurantList.description: Restaurant Adam | PURE. HONEST. PASSION. For a night of culinary bliss Restaurant Adam is the place to be. Come in to our cosy restaurant on the Overtoom in the old part of Amsterdam West en let yourself be pampered. Airconditioning is placed in the restaurant to make it comfortable in the hot days of the year. Head Chef Arne Russchen and his team prepare pure dishes full of flavour. Always seasonal and made with love.
restaurantList.address: Overtoom 515a, 1054 LH Amsterdam The Netherlands

restaurantList.name: Gartine
restaurantList.description: In the middle of the busy city centre (close to Spui) of Amsterdam you can enjoy a quiet and delicious breakfast, lunch or high tea at Gartine. We have place for a maximum of twenty-four people. Our products come directly from our own kitchen garden! We support the foundation ‘Adopteer een kip’ and work with organic eggs. On our menu you can find authentic regional products that meet the criteria from the Slow Food organisation.

photo.caption: Gartine serveert gerechten met groenten en fruit uit eigen moestuin. Voor een ontbijt, lunch en high-tea.

restaurantList.address: Taksteeg 7, 1012 PB Amsterdam The Netherlands

restaurantList.name: Bistrot des Alpes
restaurantList.description: A complete Alpine experience and French refined cuisine Decorated like a French Alp chalet, Bistrot des Alpes offers a complete Alpine experience. Chef Thibault prepares typical French Alp dishes and a menu inspired on the French kitchen. You can taste in Bistrot des Alpes the Cheesefondue, Raclette and Tartiflette or our more refined seasonal menu based on the French gastronomie.
restaurantList.address: Utrechtsedwarsstraat 141, 1017 WE Amsterdam The Netherlands

restaurantList.name: Mr. Meat
restaurantList.description: MR. MEAT I have gained experience in different flavors to make the best. It has been my greatest passion to provide the best to You. While presenting my unique flavors, I also considered your comfort and created delightful places. All you need to do is to just enjoy yourselves! Let's Meat Here!
restaurantList.address: Haarlemmerstraat 118, 1013 EX Amsterdam The Netherlands

restaurantList.name: Restaurant Olijfje
restaurantList.address: Valkenburgerstraat 223D 1068 Gv, 1011 MJ Amsterdam The Netherlands

restaurantList.name: Grand Cafe 1884
restaurantList.description: The building in which Grand Café 1884 is located, called "de Zeevaart", has been empty for years. After a renovation of more than a year we have opened a Grand Café / Restaurant with a beautiful terrace overlooking the IJ that serves as a meeting place and as a perfect location for breakfast, lunch, drinks or dinner. We are open 7 days a week. Our visitors mainly mention the excellent cuisine and delicious dishes and the professional and friendly service. Something that we are very proud of and in which we want to continue to exceed ourselves.
restaurantList.address: De Ruyterkade 105, 1011 AB Amsterdam The Netherlands

restaurantList.name: Staring at Jacob
restaurantList.description: Cozy neighbourhood cafe serving original American brunch. Nice sunny terrace.
restaurantList.address: Jacob Van Lennepkade 215, 1054 ZP Amsterdam The Netherlands

restaurantList.name: Eastwood Beer & Grill
restaurantList.description: Have a drink, meal or bite. Whatever you feel like. Be surprised, come and visit us to see how we change our breakfast and lunch restaurant into a more intimate Beer & Grill restaurant. Grilled on our broiler, we serve meat, fish and vegetarian dishes. Straight from the tap or bottle, brewed in Amsterdam or somewhere else, we serve local and international beers matching with the dishes on the menu. Reservations can be made via our website.
restaurantList.address: Oosterdoksstraat 4 DoubleTree by Hilton Amsterdam Centraal Station, 1011 DK Amsterdam The Netherlands

restaurantList.name: The Burger Room
restaurantList.description: We are a Burger Restaurant and Cocktail bar inspired by The Wizard Of Oz located in the heart of Amsterdams Fashion and Museum District. We serve top-notch burgers made of prime beef and cocktails stirred and shaken by our mixologists. Our cocktailbar is open for everyone with or without reservation! ( 12.00 AM - 10.00 PM) *** CHILDREN ARE WELCOME FROM THE AGE OF FIVE *** Besides prime beef burgers, we also serve a range of bar bites, salads, wizardly delicious milkshakes and desserts. Don't forget to check out the famous mini museum downstairs at our restaurant, where you may find a replica of" Dorothys Ruby Slippers” from the world famous movie, The Wizard Of Oz. See you soon, and don’t forget: Oz is just around the Corner!
restaurantList.address: Paulus Potterstraat 30H In Front of The Main Entrance Of Van Gogh museum, 1071 DA Amsterdam The Netherlands

restaurantList.name: Brasserie Ambassade
restaurantList.description: Come in for a delicious breakfast, lunch and/or dinner in our beautiful Brasserie Ambassade - part of the Ambassade Hotel - situated on the Herengracht canal in the centre of Amsterdam. Enjoy French cuisine with a modern twist while being surrounded by colourful paintings from famous CoBrA-artists. Or, have a seat on our canal view terrace overlooking the Herengracht! At Brasserie Ambassade, the emphasis lies on fresh, seasonal, artisanal and local products. Executive Chef Tom van Buuren and his team offer a delicious and versatile à la carte menu of French dishes with a modern twist. Our ‘Ambassadors’ also serve a fine selection of flavorful wines. The team of Brasserie Ambassade looks forward to welcoming you!

photo.caption: The view on Brasserie Ambassade and Ambassade Hotel from Herengracht

restaurantList.address: Herengracht 339, 1016 AZ Amsterdam The Netherlands

restaurantList.name: Lumbini Indian & Nepalese Restaurant
restaurantList.description: Are you looking for an Indian and Nepalese restaurant in the center of Amsterdam? Then take a look at Lumbini Restaurant! We have always believed that Indian and Nepalese cuisines are all about the fine balance between sweet, sour, Pungent and spicy food. To get this balance right, we have the dishes being prepared by professional chef. We do everything in the proper manner to ensure that you get to experience the authentic appetizers, Tandoori grill and Curries.
restaurantList.address: Amstel 32 H, 1017 AB Amsterdam The Netherlands

restaurantList.name: PIQNIQ
restaurantList.description: PIQNIQ: for your breakfast, lunch & high tea in the Jordaan area in Amsterdam. PIQNIQ refers to a variety of small dishes of which you can choose from, just like a picnic in the country. At PIQNIQ you are invited to choose from our variety of small sweet & savory dishes and enjoying them in our nice natural restaurant..At PIQNIQ we serve breakfast, lunch, coffee and tea with sweet bites, fresh juices, smoothies, a quality glass of wine and cold beers. You can also order for a special treat at the office or to take with you to the park or on your boat tour. Take a look at our website for the different possibilities and the menu. We are closed during the corona crisis ut hope to be open soon. Daily from 09.00 am. till 05:30 pm.
restaurantList.address: Lindengracht 59 hs, 1015 KC Amsterdam The Netherlands

activityList.name: Rijksmuseum
activityList.description: The Rijksmuseum is the museum of the Netherlands. The completely renovated Rijksmuseum tells the story of the Netherlands from the Middle Ages to the 20th century. Including works by Rembrandt, Vermeer, Frans Hals, and more! Most famous is Rembrandt's masterpiece the Night Watch. A new display of the collection, a renewed building, new public facilities, a revamped garden and a new Asian Pavilion. Open daily from 9 am to 5 pm.
activityList.ranking: #2 of 944 things to do in Amsterdam

activityList.name: Anne Frank House
activityList.description: The Anne Frank House (Dutch: Anne Frank Huis) is a museum dedicated to Jewish wartime diarist Anne Frank. The building is located on a canal called the Prinsengracht, close to the Westerkerk, in central Amsterdam in the Netherlands. As a visitor, you experience this story through a audio tour, quotes, photos, videos, and original items. The Anne Frank House can only be visited with an online ticket for a specific date and time.
activityList.ranking: #1 of 944 things to do in Amsterdam
activityList.address: Prinsengracht 263 - 267 museum entrance Westermarkt 20, 1016 DK Amsterdam The Netherlands

activityList.name: Van Gogh Museum
activityList.description: Discover the world's largest collection of works by Dutch painter Vincent van Gogh, featuring masterpieces such as Sunflowers, The Potato Eaters, Almond Blossom and The Bedroom. Book your tickets online. Please consult the museum website for current opening hours.

Van Gogh Museum

activityList.name: The Jordaan
activityList.description: This charming neighborhood is Amsterdam's Greenwich Village, with its narrow alleys, leafy canals lined with 17th-century houses, quirky specialty shops, cafes and designer boutiques.
activityList.ranking: #4 of 944 things to do in Amsterdam

activityList.name: A'dam Lookout
activityList.description: LOOKOUT 360º Amsterdam + sensational swing An iconic viewing point in The Netherlands - A’DAM LOOKOUT, has joined the Eiffel Tower, the Fernsehturm and the London Eye. For the daredevils among us, LOOKOUT also has a further adrenalin kick in store. On the roof is Europe’s highest swing. You swing over the edge of the tower at a thrilling height of almost 100 metres above the ground. Highlights: - The most spectacular view of Amsterdam and the surrounding area - A Bird’s-eye view of Amsterdam from the highest swing in Europe - Access to the indoor interactive state-of-the-art Amsterdam exhibition - Free digital photo of your visit to LOOKOUT - Enjoy coffee, breakfast, lunch, dinner and/or cocktails in Madam Restaurant & Sky Bar - Free WIFI available Payments with cards only.
activityList.ranking: #37 of 944 things to do in Amsterdam
